<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.research.att.com/projects/OEIS?Anum=A057752" class="external text" title="http://www.research.att.com/projects/OEIS?Anum=A057752" rel="nofollow">"Difference between Li(10^n) and Pi(10^n), where Li(x) = integral of log(x) and Pi(x) = number of primes &lt;= x (A057752)"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/On-Line_Encyclopedia_of_Integer_Sequences" title="On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences">On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences</a></i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.research.att.com/projects/OEIS?Anum=A057752" class="external free" title="http://www.research.att.com/projects/OEIS?Anum=A057752" rel="nofollow">http://www.research.att.com/projects/OEIS?Anum=A057752</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Difference+between+Li%2810%5En%29+and+Pi%2810%5En%29%2C+where+Li%28x%29+%3D+integral+of+log%28x%29+and+Pi%28x%29+%3D+number+of+primes+%3C%3D+x+%28A057752%29&amp;rft.atitle=%5B%5BOn-Line+Encyclopedia+of+Integer+Sequences%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.research.att.com%2Fprojects%2FOEIS%3FAnum%3DA057752&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Prime_number_theorem"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ol>
